Maven Java Web Application (CI/CD Pipeline)

 Project Overview

This repository contains a Java-based web application managed with Maven. It is designed as a centerpiece for a modern DevOps CI/CD pipeline, demonstrating automated building, testing, containerization, and deployment.

 Tech Stack

Language: Java (JDK 8)

Build Tool: Apache Maven

CI/CD: Jenkins (Pipeline-as-Code)

Containerization: Docker

Artifact Management: SonarQube (Static Analysis)

Deployment: Apache Tomcat / AWS EC2

Key Features

Automated Build: Uses pom.xml to manage dependencies and build the .war artifact.

Jenkins Integration: Multiple Jenkinsfiles (Scripted and Declarative) to handle automated testing and deployment.

Dockerized: Includes a Dockerfile to package the application into a lightweight, portable container.

Financial Mindset: Configured for cost-effective deployment on AWS using optimized EC2 instances

 CI/CD Workflow

Code: Developer pushes changes to GitHub.

Build: Jenkins triggers a build using mvn clean package.

Analyze: Code quality check via SonarQube.

Package: Docker image is built and pushed to Docker Hub.

Deploy: Application is deployed to a Tomcat server


Prerequisites

Java JDK 8 or higher

Maven 3.8.6

Docker installed (for containerization)

Local Build

To compile the code and generate the WAR file locally:

Bash

git clone https://github.com/JimmyT96/maven-web-application.git cd maven-web-application mvn clean package 

The artifact will be located in the /target directory.

Running with Docker

Bash

docker build -t maven-web-app . docker run -p 8080:8080 maven-web-app 

